message.content: The registry key "Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Winlogon" contains values related to system logon settings. In this case, the "Userinit" value shows an unusual addition of "C:\WINDOWS\system32\sdra64.exe" alongside the legitimate "C:\WINDOWS\system32\userinit.exe". This alteration could indicate malicious activity, as the added executable may be part of the payload causing the security features and system file protections to be disabled. Further analysis of "sdra64.exe" is recommended to determine its nature and potential threat to the system.
